    "summary": "Natural logarithm",
    "description": "The natural logarithm is the logarithm to the base *e* of the number `x`. This process is an alias for the *log* process with the base set to *e*: `log(x, e())`. The natural logarithm is the inverse function of taking *e* to the power x.\n\nThe no-data value `null` is passed through.\n\nThe computations follow [IEEE Standard 754](https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/8766229) whenever the processing environment supports it. Therefore, `ln(0)` results in Â±infinity if the processing environment supports it or otherwise an error is thrown.",
